### Customer self-service booking routes (/me/holds, /me/reservations*,
### /me/credits, /me/push-tokens, /me/reservations/{id}/wallet-pass)
###
### These power the customer-facing mobile app. All require a CUSTOMER
### access token (issued by /auth/customer/verify). API Gateway uses the
### customer-only authorizer; the Lambda re-checks ownership via
### requireCustomerOwnership + per-route resource ownership.
###
### Pre-existing /me routes (profile, list reservations, delete account)
### are documented separately in me.http.
###
### Requires: {{baseUrl}}, {{customerAccessToken}}, {{eventDate}},
###           {{tableId}}, {{holdId}}, {{reservationId}}, {{squareSourceId}}
###           in http-client env.

### POST /me/holds — create a customer-owned hold (rate-limited:
### 5 holds per 5 minutes per Cognito sub).
### Body: { eventDate, tableId }
### → 201 { item: { ..., customerCognitoSub }, ttlSeconds: 600 }
### → 429 if the customer-hold rate-limit window is full
POST {{baseUrl}}/me/holds
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventDate": "{{eventDate}}",
  "tableId": "{{tableId}}"
}

### POST /me/reservations — upgrade your own hold to a reservation.
### customerName must come in the body; phone is read from Cognito.
### Body: { eventDate, tableId, holdId, customerName }
### → 201 { item: { reservationId, ..., customerCognitoSub } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/me/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventDate": "{{eventDate}}",
  "tableId": "{{tableId}}",
  "holdId": "{{holdId}}",
  "customerName": "Alice Test"
}

### POST /me/reservations/{id}/payment/square — pay your own deposit
### via Square In-App Payments SDK (sourceId is the device-tokenized
### card or wallet nonce).
### Body: { eventDate, sourceId, amount, idempotencyKey? }
### → 200 { ok, reservation, square: { paymentId, status, receiptUrl } }
### → 502 with auto-refund result if Square charged but record failed
###   (audit C2 safety net)
POST {{baseUrl}}/me/reservations/{{reservationId}}/payment/square
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventDate": "{{eventDate}}",
  "sourceId": "{{squareSourceId}}",
  "amount": 100,
  "idempotencyKey": "smoke-test-1"
}

### PUT /me/reservations/{id}/cancel — self-cancel ≥24h before event
### end-of-day UTC (per locked policy 2026-05-10). Always issues a
### RESCHEDULE_CREDIT (refunds are staff-only).
### Body: { eventDate, reason? }
### → 200 { item: cancelled reservation }
### → 409 with { policyHours: 24 } when within the 24h window
PUT {{baseUrl}}/me/reservations/{{reservationId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventDate": "{{eventDate}}",
  "reason": "Plans changed"
}

### GET /me/reservations/{id}/check-in-pass — re-fetch your own pass
### without needing the SMS'd token. Reservation must be CONFIRMED+PAID
### for an active pass to exist; otherwise 404 PASS_NOT_READY.
### → 200 { pass: { passId, token, qr, expiresAt, ... } }
GET {{baseUrl}}/me/reservations/{{reservationId}}/check-in-pass?eventDate={{eventDate}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}

### POST /me/reservations/{id}/wallet-pass — Apple Wallet .pkpass.
### SCAFFOLD: returns 501 WALLET_PASS_NOT_CONFIGURED until Apple Pass
### Type ID cert is provisioned + signing endpoint is implemented.
### Mobile app should hide the "Add to Wallet" CTA when this returns 501.
POST {{baseUrl}}/me/reservations/{{reservationId}}/wallet-pass
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventDate": "{{eventDate}}"
}

### GET /me/credits — reschedule credit balance for the caller's phone.
### → 200 { items: [...curated credits], totalRemaining }
GET {{baseUrl}}/me/credits
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}

### POST /me/push-tokens — register an Expo push token for this device.
### Body: { token: "ExponentPushToken[...]", platform: "ios" | "android" }
### → 201 { registered: true, tokenHash, platform }
POST {{baseUrl}}/me/push-tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "ExponentPushToken[xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx]",
  "platform": "ios"
}

### DELETE /me/push-tokens/{token} — unregister on logout / device
### change. The token is URL-encoded in the path. Hash is computed
### server-side; the same token always maps to the same row.
### → 200 { unregistered: true, tokenHash }
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/me/push-tokens/ExponentPushToken%5Bxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx%5D
Authorization: Bearer {{customerAccessToken}}
